CTM Solution

Type: object

Common Transmission Model (CTM) Solution Schema v0.1

root ctm_version
Type: string

release version of CTM specification

root solution
Type: object

structure to hold persistent solution data

root solution global_params
Type: object

structure to hold global settings for parameters in the network

root solution global_params unit_convention
Type: enum (of string)

units used for physical network parameters

Must be one of:

  • "NATURAL_UNITS"
  • "PER_UNIT_COMPONENT_BASE"
  • "PER_UNIT_SYSTEM_BASE"

root solution global_params base_mva
Type: number Default: 100.0

[MVA] system-wide apparent power base

Value must be strictly greater than 0

root time_series_data
Type: object

structure to contain all time variant data of the system/case. All time series are synchronized to the same timestamps, which should should be stored using Unix time. Structure is quasi-tabular, with uid, name, pathtofile, values, and ext being arrays in the same order of said field. This is done in order to allow for better compression (e.g., using HDF5) for the values field.

root time_series_data timestamp
Type: array

[seconds] seconds since epoch (Unix time) for each instant for which time series values are provided

 No Additional Items

Each item of this array must be:

Value must be greater or equal to 0
